WEBVTT

00:02.335 --> 00:03.335
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.370 --> 00:04.903
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.441 --> 00:10.175
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:10.377 --> 00:13.212
[ Spooky circus music playing ]

00:28.095 --> 00:29.694
Mm-mm-mm.

00:29.729 --> 00:33.498
Gather round, little chillin's,
and I'll tell y'all a tale

00:33.533 --> 00:37.669
'bout a town come together
to catch its white whale.

00:37.704 --> 00:41.106
Scrappin' and scrapin'
like a bone on a file,

00:41.141 --> 00:46.412
teach a dead dog new tricks
or end up in a pile.

00:49.216 --> 00:52.184
[ Grunts ]
Okay, got to grab these.

00:52.219 --> 00:54.619
[ Humming ]
♪ Ya, ya, ya ♪

00:54.654 --> 00:56.555
♪ I just can't wait ♪

00:56.590 --> 00:59.057
♪ We'll have a midnight snack ♪

00:59.092 --> 01:00.792
♪ We're gonna stay up late ♪

01:00.827 --> 01:02.194
[ Both giggling ]

01:02.229 --> 01:03.595
♪ Sleepover ♪

01:03.630 --> 01:06.231
-Milady.
-Oh, you stop it.

01:06.266 --> 01:08.033
Oh, no.

01:08.068 --> 01:09.634
Uh, Clarence?

01:09.669 --> 01:12.270
Surprise!
We're having the big--

01:12.305 --> 01:14.773
biggest sleepover
that we ever had.

01:14.808 --> 01:16.041
Okay, yeah.

01:16.076 --> 01:18.043
You really outdone yourself
this time, Clarence, huh?

01:18.078 --> 01:21.713
Um, but don't you think it's
time to, you know, take a break?

01:21.748 --> 01:23.882
I mean, you had trivia night
on Monday,

01:23.917 --> 01:26.718
balloon bash on Tuesday,
the petting zoo on Wednesday,

01:26.753 --> 01:29.287
and the bubble bath party
last night.

01:29.322 --> 01:32.424
Those were just practice for the
biggest sleepover of all time.

01:32.459 --> 01:35.560
We'll put a bottomless ice cream
station over here

01:35.595 --> 01:38.230
and a bounce house
over there.

01:38.265 --> 01:40.398
Oh, and Chad will be
Chozo the Clown.

01:40.433 --> 01:42.834
But, what if we play
"Devils in Dixieland," huh?

01:42.869 --> 01:45.070
Just us.
♪<i> Oh, yeah</i> ♪

01:45.105 --> 01:46.738
We're gonna have
the biggest pillow fight

01:46.773 --> 01:49.741
in Aberdale history,
and all our friends will come.

01:49.776 --> 01:51.309
-Wait.
-Everyone. All our friends.

01:51.344 --> 01:52.911
[ Gasps ]
Okay. Okay, okay, okay.

01:52.946 --> 01:55.714
This is gonna top all the
sleepovers in the whole world.

01:58.552 --> 02:00.485
Clarence:<i> Come in, Jeff.</i>

02:00.520 --> 02:02.320
<i>Clarencesaurus to...Jeff.</i>

02:02.355 --> 02:03.755
It's J-Proper.

02:03.790 --> 02:06.091
<i>Jeff, you got to come</i>
<i>to my sleepover.</i>

02:06.126 --> 02:08.960
Everyone's gonna go --
Belson and Sumo

02:08.995 --> 02:11.263
and, um, Ms. Baker
and Mr. Reese,

02:11.298 --> 02:13.765
and we're all gonna sleep
in one room, of course.

02:13.800 --> 02:15.934
<i>And there's gonna be</i>
<i>a huge pillow fight.</i>

02:15.969 --> 02:17.469
<i>Oh, you could be</i>
<i>on my team.</i>

02:17.504 --> 02:18.970
Whoa,
slow down, Clarence.

02:19.005 --> 02:21.306
But, Jeff, this is gonna be
the biggest party

02:21.341 --> 02:23.542
you've ever
even even heard of.

02:23.577 --> 02:25.377
Yeah, that's --
[ Shudders ]

02:25.412 --> 02:26.711
That sounds overwhelming.

02:26.746 --> 02:28.780
Then I got to be "on"
all night.

02:28.815 --> 02:31.283
I'm just gonna stay home
and finish Jellyman.

02:31.318 --> 02:32.817
But thanks for the invite.

02:32.852 --> 02:34.819
Okay, but you'll be
missin' out.

02:34.854 --> 02:37.222
Bye, Jeff. I love you.
Mwah.

02:37.257 --> 02:39.357
[ Crying ]

02:39.392 --> 02:43.695
♪♪

02:43.730 --> 02:45.297
Okay.

02:45.332 --> 02:48.466
So I've got you down
as a maybe.

02:48.501 --> 02:51.403
Minnie: Sir, I believe
you have the wrong number.

02:51.438 --> 02:54.005
See ya later, maybe.
Bring a toothbrush.

02:54.040 --> 02:56.241
Hmm, who else?

02:56.276 --> 02:58.009
[ Gasps ] Sumo.

02:58.044 --> 03:01.179
Family, this is important,
so I'm only gonna do this once.

03:01.214 --> 03:04.349
Hey, Dad, can I go to Clarence's
for a sleepover?

03:04.384 --> 03:08.520
Negative. Tonight we're doin'
radioactive preparation.

03:08.555 --> 03:12.490
Sorry, my dad is makin' us do
these stupid doomsday drills.

03:12.525 --> 03:14.659
Last time he got like this,
it lasted for two --

03:14.694 --> 03:15.927
[ Animal chomps ]
Ow!

03:15.962 --> 03:18.163
Quit blabbing
about slumber parties.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.532
-I'm coming.
-Wait, so now you are coming?

03:20.567 --> 03:22.500
What? No, I was talking
to my dad.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.269
Sumo, this could save your --

03:24.304 --> 03:26.338
[ Laughing ]

03:26.373 --> 03:29.908
Ms. Baker: Clarence, that is
so sweet of you to invite me,

03:29.943 --> 03:32.177
but I-I think you kids would
feel a little weird

03:32.212 --> 03:33.912
with a teacher
at your little sleepover.

03:33.947 --> 03:35.680
Nuh-unh.
It's not weird.

03:35.715 --> 03:37.015
We love you, Ms. Baker.

03:37.050 --> 03:39.551
You're the nicest
and funniest teacher.

03:39.586 --> 03:41.620
[ Sighs ]
- I am gonna miss you kids.

03:41.655 --> 03:45.090
-Miss us?
-I-I can't. Bye, Clarence.

03:45.125 --> 03:47.726
Beauford, tell Mama she's doing
the right thing, huh?

03:47.761 --> 03:49.061
Mrow.

03:53.066 --> 03:56.234
Guess everyone's busy.

03:56.269 --> 03:57.936
[ Sighs ]

03:59.906 --> 04:02.574
[ Farts ]
[ Gasps ] Oh. Belson.

04:06.746 --> 04:09.547
Let's see. What time is it?

04:09.582 --> 04:13.385
Now, you think you're real
funny, Mr. Noles.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.487
Don't ya? Oh.

04:15.522 --> 04:17.756
[ Snickering ]
Classic.

04:17.791 --> 04:20.558
Well, don't think the symbolism
is lost on me.

04:20.593 --> 04:22.727
This room is a temple
of discipline,

04:22.762 --> 04:24.896
a sanctuary
of civil order.

04:24.931 --> 04:27.799
And filling it with --
with these bags?

04:27.834 --> 04:30.001
Well, it's pretty clear
that you take this sacred place

04:30.036 --> 04:31.603
for a common
truck stop restroom.

04:31.638 --> 04:34.906
[ Snickers ]
Ohh, what's that smell?

04:34.941 --> 04:36.741
That's not you,
is it, Mr. Reese?

04:36.776 --> 04:38.910
You think you pranked me
real good.

04:38.945 --> 04:41.313
But when you burn me,
you burn yourself.

04:41.348 --> 04:43.415
[ Telephone rings ]

04:43.450 --> 04:46.017
[ Grunting ]

04:46.052 --> 04:47.419
[ Snickering ]

04:47.454 --> 04:50.488
[ Clears throat ] Clarence,
why are you calling here?

04:50.523 --> 04:51.956
Is Belson there?

04:51.991 --> 04:54.092
I want to invite him
to my big sleepover tonight.

04:54.127 --> 04:56.861
Actually, you can come too
if you want.

04:56.896 --> 04:59.631
Ha. That sounds like
a barrel of laughs,

04:59.666 --> 05:01.266
and it's nice of you
to phone, Clarence.

05:01.301 --> 05:04.836
But I'm afraid Mr. Noles and I
cannot attend a sleepover,

05:04.871 --> 05:07.806
because Mr. Noles
has broken the rules

05:07.841 --> 05:10.709
and is serving his sentence
as rule-breakers do.

05:10.744 --> 05:13.845
This detention's over
in 45 minutes.

05:13.880 --> 05:16.448
Quiet, Noles!
No sleepover for you.

05:16.483 --> 05:19.451
Now, if Mr. Noles had been a
more abiding citizen,

05:19.486 --> 05:22.554
he'd be free to have sleepovers
and laugh and dance

05:22.589 --> 05:25.490
with your good friend Clarence
until you could dance no longer.

05:25.525 --> 05:28.126
But instead you thought it'd be
funny to fill this room with --

05:28.161 --> 05:30.729
Hey, you stop that!
You stop that right now.

05:30.764 --> 05:32.731
What's that, stop this?

05:32.766 --> 05:34.499
Oh. I did it again.

05:34.534 --> 05:36.835
Oh, no.
I can't control myself.

05:36.870 --> 05:39.204
Keep it up. You keep laughing,
but it's not funny.

05:39.239 --> 05:41.473
Dang, guess everyone's
just too busy today

05:41.508 --> 05:43.808
for a big ol' sleepover.

05:43.843 --> 05:45.910
Funny how that works out.

05:45.945 --> 05:49.180
Oh, well.
More sleepover fun for me.

05:49.215 --> 05:50.348
[ Chuckles ]

05:50.383 --> 05:52.250
And then they opened the door

05:52.285 --> 05:56.554
to reveal the spooky,
scary ghost janitor!

05:56.589 --> 05:58.256
Aah!

05:58.291 --> 05:59.891
Hmm. Boo.

05:59.926 --> 06:02.994
Okay, round and round it goes.

06:03.029 --> 06:05.163
And, you.

06:05.198 --> 06:07.999
Hmm. Let's give these guys a
chance.

06:08.034 --> 06:09.000
Mwah.

06:09.035 --> 06:10.368
Mwah, mwah.

06:10.403 --> 06:12.237
Mwah.

06:12.272 --> 06:13.671
[ Sighs ]

06:13.706 --> 06:15.240
Uh-oh. Look out.

06:15.275 --> 06:17.175
It's a pillow fight.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.878
Ha.

06:19.913 --> 06:21.079
Huh.

06:21.114 --> 06:22.414
Popcorn.

06:22.449 --> 06:25.850
Get your popcorn here.

06:25.885 --> 06:27.519
Eat it.
[ Grunts ]

06:27.554 --> 06:30.188
♪<i> Mm, mm, mm's,</i>
<i>we live inside your bed</i> ♪

06:30.223 --> 06:33.191
♪ We're Mm's, we're Mm's ♪ ♪<i> We live
inside your socks, we're Mm's</i> ♪

06:33.226 --> 06:35.026
♪ We're super, super fun ♪
♪<i> We're super, super fun</i> ♪

06:35.061 --> 06:36.728
Mary: Okay, hon. How 'bout
we take a little break

06:36.763 --> 06:38.263
from the sleepover fun
for now, huh?

06:38.298 --> 06:41.199
What sleepover? I called
every single one of my friends.

06:41.234 --> 06:44.903
And I made all the beds
and sleepover stuff and popcorn

06:44.938 --> 06:47.372
and games,
and I put on the Mm's,

06:47.407 --> 06:51.075
and this is the smallest
giant sleepover ever.

06:51.110 --> 06:53.745
Well, you did do an amazing job
on the house,

06:53.780 --> 06:55.647
but if we settle down
a little bit,

06:55.682 --> 06:59.050
maybe we can work
something out, huh?

06:59.085 --> 07:01.453
Mary: You know, sometimes
life throws you some curveballs,

07:01.488 --> 07:05.056
but maybe you can learn to have
fun, uh, with those curveballs.

07:05.091 --> 07:08.827
Yeah, huh?
Hit it.

07:08.862 --> 07:10.995
I'll -- I'll tell ya what.
We can stay up all night.

07:11.030 --> 07:13.465
We could build pillow forts
and tell scary stories.

07:13.500 --> 07:15.733
We'll have our own sleepover.
How's that sound?

07:15.768 --> 07:18.069
[ Grumbling ]

07:18.104 --> 07:19.337
Hey, now that it's just us,

07:19.372 --> 07:21.239
maybe you can invite
one friend over, huh,

07:21.274 --> 07:22.574
like -- like Jeff
or somethin'.

07:22.609 --> 07:23.775
Oh, yeah.

07:23.810 --> 07:25.977
That kid's a clean man.
What a relief.

07:26.012 --> 07:27.912
Ugh, I was worried
- about havin' all those guests

07:27.947 --> 07:30.448
and havin' to clean
mac and cheese off the...

07:30.483 --> 07:32.016
[ Ding! ]
Yeah.

07:32.051 --> 07:34.586
I bet Jeff will want to come
now that it's not so huge.

07:34.621 --> 07:36.821
I'll go tell him.
[ Chuckling ]

07:36.856 --> 07:38.756
Ugh. Thank goodness.

07:38.791 --> 07:40.625
Yeah, that guy
never makes a mess.

07:40.660 --> 07:43.495
You know, it's aspirati--
Oh, darn.

07:43.530 --> 07:45.997
Jeff!

07:46.032 --> 07:48.833
Oh, geez. Come on. Get in here.

07:48.868 --> 07:51.336
Come in Jeff --
I-I mean J-Proper.

07:51.371 --> 07:53.671
<i>There's been a slight</i>
<i>change of plans,</i>

07:53.706 --> 07:56.174
um, 'cause no one else
is coming.

07:56.209 --> 07:58.142
<i>So, do you want</i>
<i>to come over?</i>

07:58.177 --> 08:00.612
Wow. Well, that is
quite a change,

08:00.647 --> 08:02.280
but I don't know.

08:02.315 --> 08:04.115
<i>Come on, Jeff.</i>
<i>You got to do it.</i>

08:04.150 --> 08:06.317
<i>I'm gonna go pick up</i>
<i>some snackies for us</i>

08:06.352 --> 08:08.620
<i>and your favorite</i>
<i>slimy raisin drink.</i>

08:08.655 --> 08:10.455
Well, can I bring my kite?

08:10.490 --> 08:11.956
<i>Definitely bring your kite.</i>

08:11.991 --> 08:14.025
Bring the biggest kite
you've got.

08:14.060 --> 08:15.393
Mwah.

08:15.428 --> 08:17.228
Yes, I got Jeff to come.

08:17.263 --> 08:19.931
At least that's better
than nobody.

08:22.535 --> 08:24.302
[ Chuckles ]

08:24.337 --> 08:26.571
[ Grunting ]

08:26.606 --> 08:29.841
♪♪

08:37.250 --> 08:39.484
And now for a quick
weather update.

08:39.519 --> 08:43.187
I'm here just north of Aberdale,
and it's just awful.

08:43.222 --> 08:44.756
I've never seen
anything like it.

08:44.791 --> 08:47.992
Aah! I can now report hail.
The storm is headed south.

08:48.027 --> 08:50.161
We're putting a severe weather
alert in effect.

08:50.196 --> 08:52.063
Do not go outside
under any circ--

08:52.098 --> 08:53.565
[ Laughs ]
And now moving on

08:53.600 --> 08:57.168
to this weekend's
bingo numbers!

08:57.203 --> 08:59.671
Oh, gosh.
- I don't know where to start.

08:59.706 --> 09:02.774
Yeah, this is gonna be
a real doozy to clean up.

09:02.809 --> 09:04.375
True.
But it's not every day

09:04.410 --> 09:07.278
we can have a luxury mattress to
enjoy in our living room, huh?

09:07.313 --> 09:10.014
[ Sighs ]
- This is actually really nice.

09:10.049 --> 09:13.718
Yeah, maybe the little guy's
really onto something here.

09:13.753 --> 09:15.520
I really got to get
some new bras.

09:15.555 --> 09:17.589
[ Chuckles ]
Hmm. Yeah.

09:17.624 --> 09:20.258
[ Yawns ]

09:20.293 --> 09:21.359
[ Sighs ]

09:21.394 --> 09:22.927
[ Snoring ]

09:22.962 --> 09:24.429
This place
is dirtier than usual.

09:24.464 --> 09:27.532
[ Both scream ]
Oh. Uh, I'm sorry.

09:27.567 --> 09:28.866
Is Clarence here?

09:28.901 --> 09:31.035
Uh, he's in his room,
I believe.

09:31.070 --> 09:32.604
I already checked.
He's not in there.

09:32.639 --> 09:35.440
He's probably in the garage.
I'll go check on him.

09:43.783 --> 09:45.283
♪<i> Oh</i> ♪

09:45.318 --> 09:48.086
All:
♪ We are the mattress dudes ♪

09:48.121 --> 09:51.089
♪ You'll go to sleep
with a smile ♪

09:51.124 --> 09:52.957
-Tomorrow.
-Tomorrow.

09:52.992 --> 09:54.892
Raining, raining, raining,
raining

09:54.927 --> 09:58.329
All right, I better go help
find the little guy.

09:58.364 --> 10:01.466
Me...too.

10:01.501 --> 10:04.536
♪♪

10:07.940 --> 10:09.440
Perfect conditions.

10:09.475 --> 10:11.543
[ Inhales deeply ]

10:16.115 --> 10:18.116
Fly, Jellyman. Fly.

10:18.151 --> 10:20.118
Ooh.
[ Chuckles ]

10:22.455 --> 10:23.555
Aah!

10:26.025 --> 10:27.492
Clarence? Oh.

10:27.527 --> 10:30.928
Come on out.

10:30.963 --> 10:33.264
-What?
-Just gonna -- oof.

10:33.299 --> 10:36.468
Mom, can I come --
Oh, no!

10:38.037 --> 10:40.938
Oh, Jeffery, what have you done?

10:40.973 --> 10:43.775
[ Thunder crashes ]
Uh --

10:43.810 --> 10:47.612
Balance:
What, indeed, what, indeed --

10:47.647 --> 10:50.114
left a town in the dark.

10:50.149 --> 10:52.817
Blind leading the blind,

10:52.852 --> 10:56.154
like Cave Fish and Tommy Cots --

10:56.189 --> 10:59.090
a village left behind.

11:03.796 --> 11:05.563
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:07.166 --> 11:09.234
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:10.770 --> 11:13.605
♪ Pickin' my nose ♪
